nes - After parting ways with his management group, Carlos Yulo plans to keep his focus on his medal bid for the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 334, \"end\": 345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Yulo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Yulo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Yulo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Yulo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In what seemed liked another distraction - amidcontroversiesinvolving his family, love life, and alleged performance dip - the Philippine gymnastics star said he's nearing his \\\"success rate\\\" just two months before the world's biggest sporting event.\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 661, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yulo had ended his relations with KG Management Inc., which was formed by his former Japanese coach Munehiro Kugimiya, the Gymnastics Association of the Philippines (GAP) announced in a statement on Saturday, May 11.\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 748, \"end\": 756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9987295597974813, \"rank\": 0.0006850685717899989, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 786, \"end\": 796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.700496083665488, \"rank\": 0.42753967464032555, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\"}, {\"begin\": 816, \"end\": 827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999999971701072, \"rank\": 2.563582514896913e-09, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 829, \"end\": 832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gap_Inc.\", \"score\": 0.9999999957572072, \"rank\": 4.08344790729381e-09, \"text\": \"GAP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gap_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gap_Inc.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Yulo \\\"will continue to fulfill his endorsement obligations under current contracts,\\\" the statement signed by GAP president Cynthia Carrion said.\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 994, \"end\": 997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gap_Inc.\", \"score\": 0.9999999957572072, \"rank\": 4.08344790729381e-09, \"text\": \"GAP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gap_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gap_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 1008, \"end\": 1015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cynthia_Lennon\", \"score\": 0.9998084024011097, \"rank\": 0.0001916343038639756, \"text\": \"Cynthia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cynthia_Lennon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cynthia_Lennon\"}, {\"begin\": 1016, \"end\": 1023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carrion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4280039357895198e-16, \"text\": \"Carrion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carrion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carrion\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In Japan, coach Mune was hands-on, but when I moved to the Philippines, a Filipino manager took over.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1035, \"end\": 1040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.999358718859737, \"rank\": 0.0003314387306635043, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/